@tom1884it,  the error msg "Fatal error: Call to undefined method PHPExcel_Chart_DataSeries::setPointMarker()" makes it evident.

You did :-
$dataSeriesValues1 = array(
            new PHPExcel_Chart_DataSeriesValues('Number', 'Inverter'.$inv.'!$B$2:$B$'.count($impianti[$imp]["inverter".$inv])),
        );

So, $dataSeriesValues1 is not an instance of  PHPExcel_Chart_DataSeriesValues, but it is an array containing the instance of PHPExcel_Chart_DataSeriesValues at the 0th index.

Hence, if you use $dataSeriesValues1 -> setPointMarker('none'); , you are not referring to the object. Try using $dataSeriesValues1 [0]->setPointMarker('none')

Also, do not use $series1 -> setPointMarker('none');. The variable $series1 is not an instance of PHPExcel_Chart_DataSeriesValues, but an instance of PHPExcel_Chart_DataSeries class. I do not know if this class contains setPointMarker() method.

Let me know if this works.
